This deletion script is best used to delete single record types that have > 1000 entries.
To set up do the following:
1.) Update the Saved Search "**DO NOT DELETE** WD NSPS | MR | Deletion Records" to show the records you want to delete. (1st note that if you select multiple records and they are out of order then it will not delete the records due to dependencies) (2nd note, if you don't use in your criteria Main Line = True then your script will error)
To run do the follow:
1.) Edit to the deployment, set Deployed = True, under parameters set Delete? = True and then save. 2.) To execute Edit the deployment, drop down the save and click Save and Execute
